    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus</strong>,<strong> </strong>then chop them in half</p><p>Tip: Alternatively, bend the woody ends of the asparagus until they snap!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>gluten free spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for an initial 7 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta has been cooking for 7 min, add the<strong> halved</strong> <strong>asparagus</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until just tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pot to a medium heat, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> butter</strong> and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then give everything a good mix up until the butter has melted</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half </strong>the<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped basil </strong>with<strong> half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>crispy bacon</strong> from the oven and chop it roughly with a sharp knife</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped bacon</strong> to the pot, give everything another good mix and cook for 1 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy bacon & lemony asparagus gluten free spaghetti</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad,</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy bacon & lemony asparagus gluten free spaghetti</strong> with the <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the salad with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and<strong> chopped basil</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lemon</strong> <strong>wedge </strong>and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
